com.versant.util
Class SessionPool

java.lang.Object
  com.versant.util.SessionPool

public class SessionPool
extends java.lang.Object

A SessionPool manages a pool of sessions. In addition to the normal session properties, the user may also specify the initial number of sessions and the maximum number of sessions. They are "initNumberOfSessions" and "maxNumberOfSessions", respectively. The default is one initial session and no limit on the maximum number.

Constructor Detail

SessionPool

public SessionPool(java.lang.String[] databaseNames,
                   java.util.Properties properties,
                   Capability capability,
                   java.lang.String sessionType,
                   java.lang.Object sessionFactory)
The SessionPool constructor.

Parameters:
databaseNames - The first element in the array is the name of the session database. The rest are the connected databases.
properties - The session properties other than the database names.
capability - The Versant Capability instance required to create a "secure" Versant/Java session.
sessionType - Valid values are "FundSession", "TransSession", "ODMGSession". The default is "ODMGSession".
sessionFactory - The session factory object.

It sets up the sessionFactory, separates the sessionPool properties from the session properties, sets up the data structure to hold the sessions, and creates the initial number of sessions.

public FundSession getSession()
Attach to any available session from the pool. The caller is responsible for calling freeSession() in order for this session to return to the free pool.
